Trichechus manatus latrisotris

Taxonomy
Phylum: Chordata
Class: Mammalia
Order: Sirenia

Key morphological traits:
- large whiskers (vibrissae) used to navigate
- Spatula-like paddle used for propulsion
- no external ear flap
- Pelage cover over grey skin
- white scar tissue

Fun fact: Populations have recently significantly decreased due to a scarcity of food. Red tides have wiped out a lot of the sea grass beds that Florida manatees previously fed on.
